EN: Please install a valve on the water pipe so that the water source can be shut off when needed.

ZH: 这条水管有异味，可能需要清洗一下。
EN: This water pipe has an odor and may need to be cleaned.

ZH: 老房子的水管有些生锈了，需要定期清理。
EN: The water pipes in the old house are rusty and need regular cleaning.

ZH: 安装水管之前，先确保有足够的防护措施。
EN: Before installing the water pipe, make sure you have enough protective measures in place.

ZH: 这是一种高质量的水管，保证使用寿命长。
EN: This is a high-quality water pipe with a long service life.

ZH: 水管需要配合合适的水龙头才能正常工作。
EN: The water pipe needs to work properly with a suitable faucet.

ZH: 反复检查水管的连接处，确保没有渗漏。
EN: Check the connections of the water pipe repeatedly to ensure there are no leaks.

ZH: 换一根更粗的水管，可以提高水压。
EN: Replacing the water pipe with a thicker one can increase water pressure.

ZH: 水管被损坏后，工程队需要挖掉地面修理。
EN: After the water pipe is damaged, the construction team needs to dig up the ground for repair.

ZH: 紧急情况下，水管可以先用胶布暂时修理。
EN: In an emergency, the water pipe can be temporarily fixed with duct tape.

ZH: 不要随意挪动厨房里的水管，以免损坏连接处。
EN: Do not move the water pipes in the kitchen at will to avoid damaging the connections.

ZH: 花园里的水管需要时常检查，防止出现问题。
EN: The water pipes in the garden need to be checked regularly to prevent problems.

ZH: 客厅装修完毕后，需要重新铺设地板下的水管。
EN: After the living room is renovated, the water pipes under the floor need to be reinstalled.

ZH: 这些水管有点老化了，可能需要更换。
EN: These water pipes are a bit aging and may need to be replaced.

ZH: 要小心防止搬动家具时碰到墙壁上的水管。
EN: Be careful not to hit the water pipes on the walls when moving furniture.
